Manager, Perfect Execution Asia Pacific (PSG/201404/01/SG)
Job ID
EPM-00007345
Country
Singapore
State/Province
Singapore
City
Singapore
Publish Start Date
Apr 7 2014
Job Level
Supervisor / Manager
|
Responsibilities:
Work with global PSG Supply Chain Perfect Execution Leader to identify, prioritize, and resource improvement project.
Facilitate cross-functional business groups/teams to drive Perfect Execution improvements in Global Supply Chain including projects in IT, Finance, HR, etc.
Facilitate Perfect Execution Value Chain projects, work with PSG and World Area Perfect Execution Leaders to leverage best practices to run and manage projects.
Analysis of market, sales data and internal performance data to identify market segmentation opportunities and recommendations for improving lead-time and service levels to internal and external customers.
Create opportunities to engage with Emerson key customers and suppliers to share Perfect Execution message and collaborate on joint improvement opportunities where appropriate.
Assist PSG Supply Chain prepare for Perfect Execution/Profit Reviews and other Emerson Management processes to ensure Perfect Execution is an integral part of our culture and reporting.
Requirements:
Degree in Business Management, Operations, Engineering Supply Chain or Materials Management; preferably with Masters in Business Management or MBA in Business Administration.
Minimum of 10 years experience in a multi-national company - Supply Chain, Manufacturing or Materials and Procurement.
Strong background / experience in Lean facilitation and driving improvement projects will be a distinct advantage.